  67 class BareValidator(object):
  68     """ Validator class. Normalizes and/or validates any mapping against a
  69     validation-schema which is provided as an argument at class instantiation
  70     or upon calling the :meth:`~cerberus.Validator.validate`,
  71     :meth:`~cerberus.Validator.validated` or
  72     :meth:`~cerberus.Validator.normalized` method. An instance itself is
  73     callable and executes a validation.
  74 
  75     All instantiation parameters are optional.
  76 
  77     There are the introspective properties :attr:`types`, :attr:`validators`,
  78     :attr:`coercers`, :attr:`default_setters`, :attr:`rules`,
  79     :attr:`normalization_rules` and :attr:`validation_rules`.
  80 
  81     The attributes reflecting the available rules are assembled considering
  82     constraints that are defined in the docstrings of rules' methods and is
  83     effectively used as validation schema for :attr:`schema`.
  84 
  85     :param schema: See :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.schema`.
  86                    Defaults to :obj:`None`.
  87     :type schema: any :term:`mapping`
  88     :param ignore_none_values: See :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.ignore_none_values`.
  89                                Defaults to ``False``.
  90     :type ignore_none_values: :class:`bool`
  91     :param allow_unknown: See :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.allow_unknown`.
  92                           Defaults to ``False``.
  93     :type allow_unknown: :class:`bool` or any :term:`mapping`
  94     :param require_all: See :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.require_all`.
  95                         Defaults to ``False``.
  96     :type require_all: :class:`bool`
  97     :param purge_unknown: See :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.purge_unknown`.
  98                           Defaults to to ``False``.
  99     :type purge_unknown: :class:`bool`
 100     :param purge_readonly: Removes all fields that are defined as ``readonly`` in the
 101                            normalization phase.
 102     :type purge_readonly: :class:`bool`
 103     :param error_handler: The error handler that formats the result of
 104                           :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.errors`.
 105                           When given as two-value tuple with an error-handler
 106                           class and a dictionary, the latter is passed to the
 107                           initialization of the error handler.
 108                           Default: :class:`~cerberus.errors.BasicErrorHandler`.
 109     :type error_handler: class or instance based on
 110                          :class:`~cerberus.errors.BaseErrorHandler` or
 111                          :class:`tuple`
 112     """  # noqa: E501

 141     def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
 142         """ The arguments will be treated as with this signature:
 143 
 144         __init__(self, schema=None, ignore_none_values=False,
 145                  allow_unknown=False, require_all=False,
 146                  purge_unknown=False, purge_readonly=False,
 147                  error_handler=errors.BasicErrorHandler)
 148         """
 149 
 150         self.document = None
 151         """ The document that is or was recently processed.
 152             Type: any :term:`mapping` """
 153         self._errors = errors.ErrorList()
 154         """ The list of errors that were encountered since the last document
 155             processing was invoked.
 156             Type: :class:`~cerberus.errors.ErrorList` """
 157         self.recent_error = None
 158         """ The last individual error that was submitted.
 159             Type: :class:`~cerberus.errors.ValidationError` """
 160         self.document_error_tree = errors.DocumentErrorTree()
 161         """ A tree representiation of encountered errors following the
 162             structure of the document.
 163             Type: :class:`~cerberus.errors.DocumentErrorTree` """
 164         self.schema_error_tree = errors.SchemaErrorTree()
 165         """ A tree representiation of encountered errors following the
 166             structure of the schema.
 167             Type: :class:`~cerberus.errors.SchemaErrorTree` """
 168         self.document_path = ()
 169         """ The path within the document to the current sub-document.
 170             Type: :class:`tuple` """
 171         self.schema_path = ()
 172         """ The path within the schema to the current sub-schema.
 173             Type: :class:`tuple` """
 174         self.update = False
 175         self.error_handler = self.__init_error_handler(kwargs)
 176         """ The error handler used to format :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.errors`
 177             and process submitted errors with
 178             :meth:`~cerberus.Validator._error`.
 179             Type: :class:`~cerberus.errors.BaseErrorHandler` """
 180         self.__store_config(args, kwargs)
 181         self.schema = kwargs.get('schema', None)
 182         self.allow_unknown = kwargs.get('allow_unknown', False)
 183         self.require_all = kwargs.get('require_all', False)
 184         self._remaining_rules = []
 185         """ Keeps track of the rules that are next in line to be evaluated
 186             during the validation of a field.
 187             Type: :class:`list` """
 188 
 189         super(BareValidator, self).__init__()

 191     @staticmethod
 192     def __init_error_handler(kwargs):
 193         error_handler = kwargs.pop('error_handler', errors.BasicErrorHandler)
 194         if isinstance(error_handler, tuple):
 195             error_handler, eh_config = error_handler
 196         else:
 197             eh_config = {}
 198         if isinstance(error_handler, type) and issubclass(
 199             error_handler, errors.BaseErrorHandler
 200         ):
 201             return error_handler(**eh_config)
 202         elif isinstance(error_handler, errors.BaseErrorHandler):
 203             return error_handler
 204         else:
 205             raise RuntimeError('Invalid error_handler.')

 207     def __store_config(self, args, kwargs):
 208         """ Assign args to kwargs and store configuration. """
 209         signature = (
 210             'schema',
 211             'ignore_none_values',
 212             'allow_unknown',
 213             'require_all',
 214             'purge_unknown',
 215             'purge_readonly',
 216         )
 217         for i, p in enumerate(signature[: len(args)]):
 218             if p in kwargs:
 219                 raise TypeError("__init__ got multiple values for argument " "'%s'" % p)
 220             else:
 221                 kwargs[p] = args[i]
 222         self._config = kwargs
 223         """ This dictionary holds the configuration arguments that were used to
 224             initialize the :class:`Validator` instance except the
 225             ``error_handler``. """

 232     def _error(self, *args):
 233         """ Creates and adds one or multiple errors.
 234 
 235         :param args: Accepts different argument's signatures.
 236 
 237                      *1. Bulk addition of errors:*
 238 
 239                      - :term:`iterable` of
 240                        :class:`~cerberus.errors.ValidationError`-instances
 241 
 242                      The errors will be added to
 243                      :attr:`~cerberus.Validator._errors`.
 244 
 245                      *2. Custom error:*
 246 
 247                      - the invalid field's name
 248 
 249                      - the error message
 250 
 251                      A custom error containing the message will be created and
 252                      added to :attr:`~cerberus.Validator._errors`.
 253                      There will however be fewer information contained in the
 254                      error (no reference to the violated rule and its
 255                      constraint).
 256 
 257                      *3. Defined error:*
 258 
 259                      - the invalid field's name
 260 
 261                      - the error-reference, see :mod:`cerberus.errors`
 262 
 263                      - arbitrary, supplemental information about the error
 264 
 265                      A :class:`~cerberus.errors.ValidationError` instance will
 266                      be created and added to
 267                      :attr:`~cerberus.Validator._errors`.
 268         """
 269         if len(args) == 1:
 270             self._errors.extend(args[0])
 271             self._errors.sort()
 272             for error in args[0]:
 273                 self.document_error_tree.add(error)
 274                 self.schema_error_tree.add(error)
 275                 self.error_handler.emit(error)
 276         elif len(args) == 2 and isinstance(args[1], _str_type):
 277             self._error(args[0], errors.CUSTOM, args[1])
 278         elif len(args) >= 2:
 279             field = args[0]
 280             code = args[1].code
 281             rule = args[1].rule
 282             info = args[2:]
 283 
 284             document_path = self.document_path + (field,)
 285 
 286             schema_path = self.schema_path
 287             if code != errors.UNKNOWN_FIELD.code and rule is not None:
 288                 schema_path += (field, rule)
 289 
 290             if not rule:
 291                 constraint = None
 292             else:
 293                 field_definitions = self._resolve_rules_set(self.schema[field])
 294                 if rule == 'nullable':
 295                     constraint = field_definitions.get(rule, False)
 296                 elif rule == 'required':
 297                     constraint = field_definitions.get(rule, self.require_all)
 298                     if rule not in field_definitions:
 299                         schema_path = "__require_all__"
 300                 else:
 301                     constraint = field_definitions[rule]
 302 
 303             value = self.document.get(field)
 304 
 305             self.recent_error = errors.ValidationError(
 306                 document_path, schema_path, code, rule, constraint, value, info
 307             )
 308             self._error([self.recent_error])

 310     def _get_child_validator(self, document_crumb=None, schema_crumb=None, **kwargs):
 311         """ Creates a new instance of Validator-(sub-)class. All initial
 312             parameters of the parent are passed to the initialization, unless
 313             a parameter is given as an explicit *keyword*-parameter.
 314 
 315         :param document_crumb: Extends the
 316                                :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.document_path`
 317                                of the child-validator.
 318         :type document_crumb: :class:`tuple` or :term:`hashable`
 319         :param schema_crumb: Extends the
 320                              :attr:`~cerberus.Validator.schema_path`
 321                              of the child-validator.
 322         :type schema_crumb: :class:`tuple` or hashable
 323         :param kwargs: Overriding keyword-arguments for initialization.
 324         :type kwargs: :class:`dict`
 325 
 326         :return: an instance of ``self.__class__``
 327         """
 328         child_config = self._config.copy()
 329         child_config.update(kwargs)
 330         if not self.is_child:
 331             child_config['is_child'] = True
 332             child_config['error_handler'] = toy_error_handler
 333             child_config['root_allow_unknown'] = self.allow_unknown
 334             child_config['root_require_all'] = self.require_all
 335             child_config['root_document'] = self.document
 336             child_config['root_schema'] = self.schema
 337 
 338         child_validator = self.__class__(**child_config)
 339 
 340         if document_crumb is None:
 341             child_validator.document_path = self.document_path
 342         else:
 343             if not isinstance(document_crumb, tuple):
 344                 document_crumb = (document_crumb,)
 345             child_validator.document_path = self.document_path + document_crumb
 346 
 347         if schema_crumb is None:
 348             child_validator.schema_path = self.schema_path
 349         else:
 350             if not isinstance(schema_crumb, tuple):
 351                 schema_crumb = (schema_crumb,)
 352             child_validator.schema_path = self.schema_path + schema_crumb
 353 
 354         return child_validator

 356     def __get_rule_handler(self, domain, rule):
 357         methodname = '_{0}_{1}'.format(domain, rule.replace(' ', '_'))
 358         result = getattr(self, methodname, None)
 359         if result is None:
 360             raise RuntimeError(
 361                 "There's no handler for '{}' in the '{}' "
 362                 "domain.".format(rule, domain)
 363             )
 364         return result

 366     def _drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(self, _errors, dp_items, sp_items):
 367         """ Removes nodes by index from an errorpath, relatively to the
 368             basepaths of self.
 369 
 370         :param errors: A list of :class:`errors.ValidationError` instances.
 371         :param dp_items: A list of integers, pointing at the nodes to drop from
 372                          the :attr:`document_path`.
 373         :param sp_items: Alike ``dp_items``, but for :attr:`schema_path`.
 374         """
 375         dp_basedepth = len(self.document_path)
 376         sp_basedepth = len(self.schema_path)
 377         for error in _errors:
 378             for i in sorted(dp_items, reverse=True):
 379                 error.document_path = drop_item_from_tuple(
 380                     error.document_path, dp_basedepth + i
 381                 )
 382             for i in sorted(sp_items, reverse=True):
 383                 error.schema_path = drop_item_from_tuple(
 384                     error.schema_path, sp_basedepth + i
 385                 )
 386             if error.child_errors:
 387                 self._drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(error.child_errors, dp_items, sp_items)

 389     def _lookup_field(self, path):
 390         """ Searches for a field as defined by path. This method is used by the
 391             ``dependency`` evaluation logic.
 392 
 393         :param path: Path elements are separated by a ``.``. A leading ``^``
 394                      indicates that the path relates to the document root,
 395                      otherwise it relates to the currently evaluated document,
 396                      which is possibly a subdocument.
 397                      The sequence ``^^`` at the start will be interpreted as a
 398                      literal ``^``.
 399         :type path: :class:`str`
 400         :returns: Either the found field name and its value or :obj:`None` for
 401                   both.
 402         :rtype: A two-value :class:`tuple`.
 403         """
 404         if path.startswith('^'):
 405             path = path[1:]
 406             context = self.document if path.startswith('^') else self.root_document
 407         else:
 408             context = self.document
 409 
 410         parts = path.split('.')
 411         for part in parts:
 412             if part not in context:
 413                 return None, None
 414             context = context.get(part, {})
 415 
 416         return parts[-1], context

 418     def _resolve_rules_set(self, rules_set):

 420             return rules_set

 574     # FIXME the returned method has the correct docstring, but doesn't appear
 575     #       in the API docs
 576     @readonly_classproperty
 577     def types(cls):
 578         """ The constraints that can be used for the 'type' rule.
 579             Type: A tuple of strings. """
 580         redundant_types = set(cls.types_mapping) & set(cls._types_from_methods)
 581         if redundant_types:
 582             warn(
 583                 "These types are defined both with a method and in the"
 584                 "'types_mapping' property of this validator: %s" % redundant_types
 585             )
 586 
 587         return tuple(cls.types_mapping) + cls._types_from_methods

 589     # Document processing
 590 
 591     def __init_processing(self, document, schema=None):
 592         self._errors = errors.ErrorList()
 593         self.recent_error = None
 594         self.document_error_tree = errors.DocumentErrorTree()
 595         self.schema_error_tree = errors.SchemaErrorTree()
 596         self.document = copy(document)
 597         if not self.is_child:
 598             self._is_normalized = False
 599 
 600         if schema is not None:
 601             self.schema = DefinitionSchema(self, schema)
 602         elif self.schema is None:
 603             if isinstance(self.allow_unknown, Mapping):
 604                 self._schema = {}
 605             else:
 606                 raise SchemaError(errors.SCHEMA_ERROR_MISSING)
 607         if document is None:
 608             raise DocumentError(errors.DOCUMENT_MISSING)
 609         if not isinstance(document, Mapping):
 610             raise DocumentError(errors.DOCUMENT_FORMAT.format(document))
 611         self.error_handler.start(self)
 612 
 613     def _drop_remaining_rules(self, *rules):
 614         """ Drops rules from the queue of the rules that still need to be
 615             evaluated for the currently processed field.
 616             If no arguments are given, the whole queue is emptied.
 617         """
 618         if rules:
 619             for rule in rules:
 620                 try:
 621                     self._remaining_rules.remove(rule)
 622                 except ValueError:
 623                     pass
 624         else:
 625             self._remaining_rules = []

 627     # # Normalizing
 628 
 629     def normalized(self, document, schema=None, always_return_document=False):
 630         """ Returns the document normalized according to the specified rules
 631         of a schema.
 632 
 633         :param document: The document to normalize.
 634         :type document: any :term:`mapping`
 635         :param schema: The validation schema. Defaults to :obj:`None`. If not
 636                        provided here, the schema must have been provided at
 637                        class instantiation.
 638         :type schema: any :term:`mapping`
 639         :param always_return_document: Return the document, even if an error
 640                                        occurred. Defaults to: ``False``.
 641         :type always_return_document: :class:`bool`
 642         :return: A normalized copy of the provided mapping or :obj:`None` if an
 643                  error occurred during normalization.
 644         """
 645         self.__init_processing(document, schema)
 646         self.__normalize_mapping(self.document, self.schema)
 647         self.error_handler.end(self)
 648         if self._errors and not always_return_document:
 649             return None
 650         else:
 651             return self.document
 652 
 653     def __normalize_mapping(self, mapping, schema):
 654         if isinstance(schema, _str_type):
 655             schema = self._resolve_schema(schema)
 656         schema = schema.copy()
 657         for field in schema:
 658             schema[field] = self._resolve_rules_set(schema[field])
 659 
 660         self.__normalize_rename_fields(mapping, schema)
 661         if self.purge_unknown and not self.allow_unknown:
 662             self._normalize_purge_unknown(mapping, schema)
 663         if self.purge_readonly:
 664             self.__normalize_purge_readonly(mapping, schema)
 665         # Check `readonly` fields before applying default values because
 666         # a field's schema definition might contain both `readonly` and
 667         # `default`.
 668         self.__validate_readonly_fields(mapping, schema)
 669         self.__normalize_default_fields(mapping, schema)
 670         self._normalize_coerce(mapping, schema)
 671         self.__normalize_containers(mapping, schema)
 672         self._is_normalized = True
 673         return mapping
 674 
 675     def _normalize_coerce(self, mapping, schema):
 676         """ {'oneof': [
 677                 {'type': 'callable'},
 678                 {'type': 'list',
 679                  'schema': {'oneof': [{'type': 'callable'},
 680                                       {'type': 'string'}]}},
 681                 {'type': 'string'}
 682                 ]} """
 683 
 684         error = errors.COERCION_FAILED
 685         for field in mapping:
 686             if field in schema and 'coerce' in schema[field]:
 687                 mapping[field] = self.__normalize_coerce(
 688                     schema[field]['coerce'],
 689                     field,
 690                     mapping[field],
 691                     schema[field].get('nullable', False),
 692                     error,
 693                 )
 694             elif (
 695                 isinstance(self.allow_unknown, Mapping)
 696                 and 'coerce' in self.allow_unknown
 697             ):
 698                 mapping[field] = self.__normalize_coerce(
 699                     self.allow_unknown['coerce'],
 700                     field,
 701                     mapping[field],
 702                     self.allow_unknown.get('nullable', False),
 703                     error,
 704                 )
 705 
 706     def __normalize_coerce(self, processor, field, value, nullable, error):
 707         if isinstance(processor, _str_type):
 708             processor = self.__get_rule_handler('normalize_coerce', processor)
 709 
 710         elif isinstance(processor, Iterable):
 711             result = value
 712             for p in processor:
 713                 result = self.__normalize_coerce(p, field, result, nullable, error)
 714                 if (
 715                     errors.COERCION_FAILED
 716                     in self.document_error_tree.fetch_errors_from(
 717                         self.document_path + (field,)
 718                     )
 719                 ):
 720                     break
 721             return result
 722 
 723         try:
 724             return processor(value)
 725         except Exception as e:
 726             if not (nullable and value is None):
 727                 self._error(field, error, str(e))
 728             return value
 729 
 730     def __normalize_containers(self, mapping, schema):
 731         for field in mapping:
 732             rules = set(schema.get(field, ()))
 733 
 734             # TODO: This check conflates validation and normalization
 735             if isinstance(mapping[field], Mapping):
 736                 if 'keysrules' in rules:
 737                     self.__normalize_mapping_per_keysrules(
 738                         field, mapping, schema[field]['keysrules']
 739                     )
 740                 if 'valuesrules' in rules:
 741                     self.__normalize_mapping_per_valuesrules(
 742                         field, mapping, schema[field]['valuesrules']
 743                     )
 744                 if rules & set(
 745                     ('allow_unknown', 'purge_unknown', 'schema')
 746                 ) or isinstance(self.allow_unknown, Mapping):
 747                     try:
 748                         self.__normalize_mapping_per_schema(field, mapping, schema)
 749                     except _SchemaRuleTypeError:
 750                         pass
 751 
 752             elif isinstance(mapping[field], _str_type):
 753                 continue
 754 
 755             elif isinstance(mapping[field], Sequence):
 756                 if 'schema' in rules:
 757                     self.__normalize_sequence_per_schema(field, mapping, schema)
 758                 elif 'items' in rules:
 759                     self.__normalize_sequence_per_items(field, mapping, schema)
 760 
 761     def __normalize_mapping_per_keysrules(self, field, mapping, property_rules):
 762         schema = dict(((k, property_rules) for k in mapping[field]))
 763         document = dict(((k, k) for k in mapping[field]))
 764         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 765             document_crumb=field, schema_crumb=(field, 'keysrules'), schema=schema
 766         )
 767         result = validator.normalized(document, always_return_document=True)
 768         if validator._errors:
 769             self._drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(validator._errors, [], [2, 4])
 770             self._error(validator._errors)
 771         for k in result:
 772             if k == result[k]:
 773                 continue
 774             if result[k] in mapping[field]:
 775                 warn(
 776                     "Normalizing keys of {path}: {key} already exists, "
 777                     "its value is replaced.".format(
 778                         path='.'.join(str(x) for x in self.document_path + (field,)),
 779                         key=k,
 780                     )
 781                 )
 782                 mapping[field][result[k]] = mapping[field][k]
 783             else:
 784                 mapping[field][result[k]] = mapping[field][k]
 785                 del mapping[field][k]
 786 
 787     def __normalize_mapping_per_valuesrules(self, field, mapping, value_rules):
 788         schema = dict(((k, value_rules) for k in mapping[field]))
 789         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 790             document_crumb=field, schema_crumb=(field, 'valuesrules'), schema=schema
 791         )
 792         mapping[field] = validator.normalized(
 793             mapping[field], always_return_document=True
 794         )
 795         if validator._errors:
 796             self._drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(validator._errors, [], [2])
 797             self._error(validator._errors)
 798 
 799     def __normalize_mapping_per_schema(self, field, mapping, schema):
 800         rules = schema.get(field, {})
 801         if not rules and isinstance(self.allow_unknown, Mapping):
 802             rules = self.allow_unknown
 803         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 804             document_crumb=field,
 805             schema_crumb=(field, 'schema'),
 806             schema=rules.get('schema', {}),
 807             allow_unknown=rules.get('allow_unknown', self.allow_unknown),  # noqa: E501
 808             purge_unknown=rules.get('purge_unknown', self.purge_unknown),
 809             require_all=rules.get('require_all', self.require_all),
 810         )  # noqa: E501
 811         value_type = type(mapping[field])
 812         result_value = validator.normalized(mapping[field], always_return_document=True)
 813         mapping[field] = value_type(result_value)
 814         if validator._errors:
 815             self._error(validator._errors)
 816 
 817     def __normalize_sequence_per_schema(self, field, mapping, schema):
 818         schema = dict(
 819             ((k, schema[field]['schema']) for k in range(len(mapping[field])))
 820         )
 821         document = dict((k, v) for k, v in enumerate(mapping[field]))
 822         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 823             document_crumb=field, schema_crumb=(field, 'schema'), schema=schema
 824         )
 825         value_type = type(mapping[field])
 826         result = validator.normalized(document, always_return_document=True)
 827         mapping[field] = value_type(result.values())
 828         if validator._errors:
 829             self._drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(validator._errors, [], [2])
 830             self._error(validator._errors)
 831 
 832     def __normalize_sequence_per_items(self, field, mapping, schema):
 833         rules, values = schema[field]['items'], mapping[field]
 834         if len(rules) != len(values):
 835             return
 836         schema = dict(((k, v) for k, v in enumerate(rules)))
 837         document = dict((k, v) for k, v in enumerate(values))
 838         validator = self._get_child_validator(
 839             document_crumb=field, schema_crumb=(field, 'items'), schema=schema
 840         )
 841         value_type = type(mapping[field])
 842         result = validator.normalized(document, always_return_document=True)
 843         mapping[field] = value_type(result.values())
 844         if validator._errors:
 845             self._drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(validator._errors, [], [2])
 846             self._error(validator._errors)

 848     @staticmethod
 849     def __normalize_purge_readonly(mapping, schema):
 850         for field in [x for x in mapping if schema.get(x, {}).get('readonly', False)]:
 851             mapping.pop(field)
 852         return mapping

 854     @staticmethod
 855     def _normalize_purge_unknown(mapping, schema):
 856         """ {'type': 'boolean'} """
 857         for field in [x for x in mapping if x not in schema]:
 858             mapping.pop(field)
 859         return mapping

 861     def __normalize_rename_fields(self, mapping, schema):
 862         for field in tuple(mapping):
 863             if field in schema:
 864                 self._normalize_rename(mapping, schema, field)
 865                 self._normalize_rename_handler(mapping, schema, field)
 866             elif (
 867                 isinstance(self.allow_unknown, Mapping)
 868                 and 'rename_handler' in self.allow_unknown
 869             ):
 870                 self._normalize_rename_handler(
 871                     mapping, {field: self.allow_unknown}, field
 872                 )
 873         return mapping
 874 
 875     def _normalize_rename(self, mapping, schema, field):
 876         """ {'type': 'hashable'} """
 877         if 'rename' in schema[field]:
 878             mapping[schema[field]['rename']] = mapping[field]
 879             del mapping[field]
 880 
 881     def _normalize_rename_handler(self, mapping, schema, field):
 882         """ {'oneof': [
 883                 {'type': 'callable'},
 884                 {'type': 'list',
 885                  'schema': {'oneof': [{'type': 'callable'},
 886                                       {'type': 'string'}]}},
 887                 {'type': 'string'}
 888                 ]} """
 889         if 'rename_handler' not in schema[field]:
 890             return
 891         new_name = self.__normalize_coerce(
 892             schema[field]['rename_handler'], field, field, False, errors.RENAMING_FAILED
 893         )
 894         if new_name != field:
 895             mapping[new_name] = mapping[field]
 896             del mapping[field]

 898     def __validate_readonly_fields(self, mapping, schema):
 899         for field in (
 900             x
 901             for x in schema
 902             if x in mapping and self._resolve_rules_set(schema[x]).get('readonly')
 903         ):
 904             self._validate_readonly(schema[field]['readonly'], field, mapping[field])
 905 
 906     def __normalize_default_fields(self, mapping, schema):
 907         empty_fields = [
 908             x
 909             for x in schema
 910             if x not in mapping
 911             or (
 912                 mapping[x] is None  # noqa: W503
 913                 and not schema[x].get('nullable', False)
 914             )  # noqa: W503
 915         ]
 916 
 917         try:
 918             fields_with_default = [x for x in empty_fields if 'default' in schema[x]]
 919         except TypeError:
 920             raise _SchemaRuleTypeError
 921         for field in fields_with_default:
 922             self._normalize_default(mapping, schema, field)
 923 
 924         known_fields_states = set()
 925         fields_with_default_setter = [
 926             x for x in empty_fields if 'default_setter' in schema[x]
 927         ]
 928         while fields_with_default_setter:
 929             field = fields_with_default_setter.pop(0)
 930             try:
 931                 self._normalize_default_setter(mapping, schema, field)
 932             except KeyError:
 933                 fields_with_default_setter.append(field)
 934             except Exception as e:
 935                 self._error(field, errors.SETTING_DEFAULT_FAILED, str(e))
 936 
 937             fields_processing_state = hash(tuple(fields_with_default_setter))
 938             if fields_processing_state in known_fields_states:
 939                 for field in fields_with_default_setter:
 940                     self._error(
 941                         field,
 942                         errors.SETTING_DEFAULT_FAILED,
 943                         'Circular dependencies of default setters.',
 944                     )
 945                 break
 946             else:
 947                 known_fields_states.add(fields_processing_state)
 948 
 949     def _normalize_default(self, mapping, schema, field):
 950         """ {'nullable': True} """
 951         mapping[field] = schema[field]['default']
 952 
 953     def _normalize_default_setter(self, mapping, schema, field):
 954         """ {'oneof': [
 955                 {'type': 'callable'},
 956                 {'type': 'string'}
 957                 ]} """
 958         if 'default_setter' in schema[field]:
 959             setter = schema[field]['default_setter']
 960             if isinstance(setter, _str_type):
 961                 setter = self.__get_rule_handler('normalize_default_setter', setter)
 962             mapping[field] = setter(mapping)

 964     # # Validating

 966     def validate(self, document, schema=None, update=False, normalize=True):
 967         """ Normalizes and validates a mapping against a validation-schema of
 968         defined rules.
 969 
 970         :param document: The document to normalize.
 971         :type document: any :term:`mapping`
 972         :param schema: The validation schema. Defaults to :obj:`None`. If not
 973                        provided here, the schema must have been provided at
 974                        class instantiation.
 975         :type schema: any :term:`mapping`
 976         :param update: If ``True``, required fields won't be checked.
 977         :type update: :class:`bool`
 978         :param normalize: If ``True``, normalize the document before validation.
 979         :type normalize: :class:`bool`
 980 
 981         :return: ``True`` if validation succeeds, otherwise ``False``. Check
 982                  the :func:`errors` property for a list of processing errors.
 983         :rtype: :class:`bool`
 984         """
 985         self.update = update
 986         self._unrequired_by_excludes = set()
 987 
 988         self.__init_processing(document, schema)
 989         if normalize:
 990             self.__normalize_mapping(self.document, self.schema)
 991 
 992         for field in self.document:
 993             if self.ignore_none_values and self.document[field] is None:
 994                 continue
 995             definitions = self.schema.get(field)
 996             if definitions is not None:
 997                 self.__validate_definitions(definitions, field)
 998             else:
 999                 self.__validate_unknown_fields(field)
1000 
1001         if not self.update:
1002             self.__validate_required_fields(self.document)
1003 
1004         self.error_handler.end(self)
1005 
1006         return not bool(self._errors)

1010     def validated(self, *args, **kwargs):
1011         """ Wrapper around :meth:`~cerberus.Validator.validate` that returns
1012             the normalized and validated document or :obj:`None` if validation
1013             failed. """
1014         always_return_document = kwargs.pop('always_return_document', False)
1015         self.validate(*args, **kwargs)
1016         if self._errors and not always_return_document:
1017             return None
1018         else:
1019             return self.document

1021     def __validate_unknown_fields(self, field):
1022         if self.allow_unknown:
1023             value = self.document[field]
1024             if isinstance(self.allow_unknown, (Mapping, _str_type)):
1025                 # validate that unknown fields matches the schema
1026                 # for unknown_fields
1027                 schema_crumb = 'allow_unknown' if self.is_child else '__allow_unknown__'
1028                 validator = self._get_child_validator(
1029                     schema_crumb=schema_crumb, schema={field: self.allow_unknown}
1030                 )
1031                 if not validator({field: value}, normalize=False):
1032                     self._error(validator._errors)
1033         else:
1034             self._error(field, errors.UNKNOWN_FIELD)

1036     def __validate_definitions(self, definitions, field):
1037         """ Validate a field's value against its defined rules. """
1038 
1039         def validate_rule(rule):
1040             validator = self.__get_rule_handler('validate', rule)
1041             return validator(definitions.get(rule, None), field, value)
1042 
1043         definitions = self._resolve_rules_set(definitions)
1044         value = self.document[field]
1045 
1046         rules_queue = [
1047             x
1048             for x in self.priority_validations
1049             if x in definitions or x in self.mandatory_validations
1050         ]
1051         rules_queue.extend(
1052             x for x in self.mandatory_validations if x not in rules_queue
1053         )
1054         rules_queue.extend(
1055             x
1056             for x in definitions
1057             if x not in rules_queue
1058             and x not in self.normalization_rules
1059             and x not in ('allow_unknown', 'require_all', 'meta', 'required')
1060         )
1061         self._remaining_rules = rules_queue
1062 
1063         while self._remaining_rules:
1064             rule = self._remaining_rules.pop(0)
1065             try:
1066                 result = validate_rule(rule)
1067                 # TODO remove on next breaking release
1068                 if result:
1069                     break
1070             except _SchemaRuleTypeError:
1071                 break
1072 
1073         self._drop_remaining_rules()

1084     def _validate_allowed(self, allowed_values, field, value):
1085         """ {'type': 'container'} """
1086         if isinstance(value, Iterable) and not isinstance(value, _str_type):
1087             unallowed = set(value) - set(allowed_values)
1088             if unallowed:
1089                 self._error(field, errors.UNALLOWED_VALUES, list(unallowed))
1090         else:
1091             if value not in allowed_values:
1092                 self._error(field, errors.UNALLOWED_VALUE, value)

1094     def _validate_check_with(self, checks, field, value):
1095         """ {'oneof': [
1096                 {'type': 'callable'},
1097                 {'type': 'list',
1098                  'schema': {'oneof': [{'type': 'callable'},
1099                                       {'type': 'string'}]}},
1100                 {'type': 'string'}
1101                 ]} """
1102         if isinstance(checks, _str_type):
1103             try:
1104                 value_checker = self.__get_rule_handler('check_with', checks)
1105             # TODO remove on next major release
1106             except RuntimeError:
1107                 value_checker = self.__get_rule_handler('validator', checks)
1108                 warn(
1109                     "The 'validator' rule was renamed to 'check_with'. Please update "
1110                     "your schema and method names accordingly.",
1111                     DeprecationWarning,
1112                 )
1113             value_checker(field, value)
1114         elif isinstance(checks, Iterable):
1115             for v in checks:
1116                 self._validate_check_with(v, field, value)
1117         else:
1118             checks(field, value, self._error)

1120     def _validate_contains(self, expected_values, field, value):
1121         """ {'empty': False } """
1122         if not isinstance(value, Iterable):
1123             return
1124 
1125         if not isinstance(expected_values, Iterable) or isinstance(
1126             expected_values, _str_type
1127         ):
1128             expected_values = set((expected_values,))
1129         else:
1130             expected_values = set(expected_values)
1131 
1132         missing_values = expected_values - set(value)
1133         if missing_values:
1134             self._error(field, errors.MISSING_MEMBERS, missing_values)

1136     def _validate_dependencies(self, dependencies, field, value):
1137         """ {'type': ('dict', 'hashable', 'list'),
1138              'check_with': 'dependencies'} """
1139         if isinstance(dependencies, _str_type) or not isinstance(
1140             dependencies, (Iterable, Mapping)
1141         ):
1142             dependencies = (dependencies,)
1143 
1144         if isinstance(dependencies, Sequence):
1145             self.__validate_dependencies_sequence(dependencies, field)
1146         elif isinstance(dependencies, Mapping):
1147             self.__validate_dependencies_mapping(dependencies, field)
1148 
1149         if (
1150             self.document_error_tree.fetch_node_from(
1151                 self.schema_path + (field, 'dependencies')
1152             )
1153             is not None
1154         ):
1155             return True

1157     def __validate_dependencies_mapping(self, dependencies, field):
1158         validated_dependencies_counter = 0
1159         error_info = {}
1160         for dependency_name, dependency_values in dependencies.items():
1161             if not isinstance(dependency_values, Sequence) or isinstance(
1162                 dependency_values, _str_type
1163             ):
1164                 dependency_values = [dependency_values]
1165 
1166             wanted_field, wanted_field_value = self._lookup_field(dependency_name)
1167             if wanted_field_value in dependency_values:
1168                 validated_dependencies_counter += 1
1169             else:
1170                 error_info.update({dependency_name: wanted_field_value})
1171 
1172         if validated_dependencies_counter != len(dependencies):
1173             self._error(field, errors.DEPENDENCIES_FIELD_VALUE, error_info)
1174 
1175     def __validate_dependencies_sequence(self, dependencies, field):
1176         for dependency in dependencies:
1177             if self._lookup_field(dependency)[0] is None:
1178                 self._error(field, errors.DEPENDENCIES_FIELD, dependency)

1180     def _validate_empty(self, empty, field, value):
1181         """ {'type': 'boolean'} """
1182         if isinstance(value, Sized) and len(value) == 0:
1183             self._drop_remaining_rules(
1184                 'allowed',
1185                 'forbidden',
1186                 'items',
1187                 'minlength',
1188                 'maxlength',
1189                 'regex',
1190                 'check_with',
1191             )
1192             if not empty:
1193                 self._error(field, errors.EMPTY_NOT_ALLOWED)

1195     def _validate_excludes(self, excluded_fields, field, value):
1196         """ {'type': ('hashable', 'list'),
1197              'schema': {'type': 'hashable'}} """
1198         if isinstance(excluded_fields, Hashable):
1199             excluded_fields = [excluded_fields]
1200 
1201         # Mark the currently evaluated field as not required for now if it actually is.
1202         # One of the so marked will be needed to pass when required fields are checked.
1203         if self.schema[field].get('required', self.require_all):
1204             self._unrequired_by_excludes.add(field)
1205 
1206         for excluded_field in excluded_fields:
1207             if excluded_field in self.schema and self.schema[field].get(
1208                 'required', self.require_all
1209             ):
1210 
1211                 self._unrequired_by_excludes.add(excluded_field)
1212 
1213         if any(excluded_field in self.document for excluded_field in excluded_fields):
1214             exclusion_str = ', '.join(
1215                 "'{0}'".format(field) for field in excluded_fields
1216             )
1217             self._error(field, errors.EXCLUDES_FIELD, exclusion_str)

1219     def _validate_forbidden(self, forbidden_values, field, value):
1220         """ {'type': 'list'} """
1221         if isinstance(value, Sequence) and not isinstance(value, _str_type):
1222             forbidden = set(value) & set(forbidden_values)
1223             if forbidden:
1224                 self._error(field, errors.FORBIDDEN_VALUES, list(forbidden))
1225         else:
1226             if value in forbidden_values:
1227                 self._error(field, errors.FORBIDDEN_VALUE, value)

1229     def _validate_items(self, items, field, values):
1230         """ {'type': 'list', 'check_with': 'items'} """
1231         if len(items) != len(values):
1232             self._error(field, errors.ITEMS_LENGTH, len(items), len(values))
1233         else:
1234             schema = dict(
1235                 (i, definition) for i, definition in enumerate(items)
1236             )  # noqa: E501
1237             validator = self._get_child_validator(
1238                 document_crumb=field,
1239                 schema_crumb=(field, 'items'),  # noqa: E501
1240                 schema=schema,
1241             )
1242             if not validator(
1243                 dict((i, value) for i, value in enumerate(values)),
1244                 update=self.update,
1245                 normalize=False,
1246             ):
1247                 self._error(field, errors.BAD_ITEMS, validator._errors)

1249     def __validate_logical(self, operator, definitions, field, value):
1250         """ Validates value against all definitions and logs errors according
1251             to the operator. """
1252         valid_counter = 0
1253         _errors = errors.ErrorList()
1254 
1255         for i, definition in enumerate(definitions):
1256             schema = {field: definition.copy()}
1257             for rule in ('allow_unknown', 'type'):
1258                 if rule not in schema[field] and rule in self.schema[field]:
1259                     schema[field][rule] = self.schema[field][rule]
1260             if 'allow_unknown' not in schema[field]:
1261                 schema[field]['allow_unknown'] = self.allow_unknown
1262 
1263             validator = self._get_child_validator(
1264                 schema_crumb=(field, operator, i), schema=schema, allow_unknown=True
1265             )
1266             if validator(self.document, update=self.update, normalize=False):
1267                 valid_counter += 1
1268             else:
1269                 self._drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(validator._errors, [], [3])
1270                 _errors.extend(validator._errors)
1271 
1272         return valid_counter, _errors

1274     def _validate_anyof(self, definitions, field, value):
1275         """ {'type': 'list', 'logical': 'anyof'} """
1276         valids, _errors = self.__validate_logical('anyof', definitions, field, value)
1277         if valids < 1:
1278             self._error(field, errors.ANYOF, _errors, valids, len(definitions))

1280     def _validate_allof(self, definitions, field, value):

1284             self._error(field, errors.ALLOF, _errors, valids, len(definitions))

1360     def _validate_readonly(self, readonly, field, value):
1361         """ {'type': 'boolean'} """
1362         if readonly:
1363             if not self._is_normalized:
1364                 self._error(field, errors.READONLY_FIELD)
1365             # If the document was normalized (and therefore already been
1366             # checked for readonly fields), we still have to return True
1367             # if an error was filed.
1368             has_error = (
1369                 errors.READONLY_FIELD
1370                 in self.document_error_tree.fetch_errors_from(
1371                     self.document_path + (field,)
1372                 )
1373             )
1374             if self._is_normalized and has_error:
1375                 self._drop_remaining_rules()

1377     def _validate_regex(self, pattern, field, value):
1378         """ {'type': 'string'} """
1379         if not isinstance(value, _str_type):
1380             return
1381         if not pattern.endswith('$'):
1382             pattern += '$'
1383         re_obj = re.compile(pattern)
1384         if not re_obj.match(value):
1385             self._error(field, errors.REGEX_MISMATCH)

1391     def __validate_required_fields(self, document):
1392         """ Validates that required fields are not missing.
1393 
1394         :param document: The document being validated.
1395         """
1396         try:
1397             required = set(
1398                 field
1399                 for field, definition in self.schema.items()
1400                 if self._resolve_rules_set(definition).get('required', self.require_all)
1401                 is True
1402             )
1403         except AttributeError:
1404             if self.is_child and self.schema_path[-1] == 'schema':
1405                 raise _SchemaRuleTypeError
1406             else:
1407                 raise
1408         required -= self._unrequired_by_excludes
1409         missing = required - set(
1410             field
1411             for field in document
1412             if document.get(field) is not None or not self.ignore_none_values
1413         )
1414 
1415         for field in missing:
1416             self._error(field, errors.REQUIRED_FIELD)
1417 
1418         # At least one field from self._unrequired_by_excludes should be present in
1419         # document.
1420         if self._unrequired_by_excludes:
1421             fields = set(field for field in document if document.get(field) is not None)
1422             if self._unrequired_by_excludes.isdisjoint(fields):
1423                 for field in self._unrequired_by_excludes - fields:
1424                     self._error(field, errors.REQUIRED_FIELD)

1426     def _validate_schema(self, schema, field, value):
1427         """ {'type': ['dict', 'string'],
1428              'anyof': [{'check_with': 'schema'},
1429                        {'check_with': 'bulk_schema'}]} """
1430         if schema is None:
1431             return
1432 
1433         if isinstance(value, Sequence) and not isinstance(value, _str_type):
1434             self.__validate_schema_sequence(field, schema, value)
1435         elif isinstance(value, Mapping):
1436             self.__validate_schema_mapping(field, schema, value)
1437 
1438     def __validate_schema_mapping(self, field, schema, value):
1439         schema = self._resolve_schema(schema)
1440         allow_unknown = self.schema[field].get('allow_unknown', self.allow_unknown)
1441         require_all = self.schema[field].get('require_all', self.require_all)
1442         validator = self._get_child_validator(
1443             document_crumb=field,
1444             schema_crumb=(field, 'schema'),
1445             schema=schema,
1446             allow_unknown=allow_unknown,
1447             require_all=require_all,
1448         )
1449         try:
1450             if not validator(value, update=self.update, normalize=False):
1451                 self._error(field, errors.MAPPING_SCHEMA, validator._errors)
1452         except _SchemaRuleTypeError:
1453             self._error(field, errors.BAD_TYPE_FOR_SCHEMA)
1454             raise
1455 
1456     def __validate_schema_sequence(self, field, schema, value):
1457         schema = dict(((i, schema) for i in range(len(value))))
1458         validator = self._get_child_validator(
1459             document_crumb=field,
1460             schema_crumb=(field, 'schema'),
1461             schema=schema,
1462             allow_unknown=self.allow_unknown,
1463         )
1464         validator(
1465             dict(((i, v) for i, v in enumerate(value))),
1466             update=self.update,
1467             normalize=False,
1468         )
1469 
1470         if validator._errors:
1471             self._drop_nodes_from_errorpaths(validator._errors, [], [2])
1472             self._error(field, errors.SEQUENCE_SCHEMA, validator._errors)

1474     def _validate_type(self, data_type, field, value):
1475         """ {'type': ['string', 'list'],
1476              'check_with': 'type'} """
1477         if not data_type:
1478             return
1479 
1480         types = (data_type,) if isinstance(data_type, _str_type) else data_type
1481 
1482         for _type in types:
1483             # TODO remove this block on next major release
1484             # this implementation still supports custom type validation methods
1485             type_definition = self.types_mapping.get(_type)
1486             if type_definition is not None:
1487                 matched = isinstance(
1488                     value, type_definition.included_types
1489                 ) and not isinstance(value, type_definition.excluded_types)
1490             else:
1491                 type_handler = self.__get_rule_handler('validate_type', _type)
1492                 matched = type_handler(value)
1493             if matched:
1494                 return
1495 
1496             # TODO uncomment this block on next major release
1497             #      when _validate_type_* methods were deprecated:
1498             # type_definition = self.types_mapping[_type]
1499             # if isinstance(value, type_definition.included_types) \
1500             #         and not isinstance(value, type_definition.excluded_types):  # noqa 501
1501             #     return
1502 
1503         self._error(field, errors.BAD_TYPE)
1504         self._drop_remaining_rules()

1525 class InspectedValidator(type):
1526     """ Metaclass for all validators """
1527 
1528     def __new__(cls, *args):
1529         if '__doc__' not in args[2]:
1530             args[2].update({'__doc__': args[1][0].__doc__})
1531         return super(InspectedValidator, cls).__new__(cls, *args)
1532 
1533     def __init__(cls, *args):
1534         def attributes_with_prefix(prefix):
1535             return tuple(
1536                 x[len(prefix) + 2 :]
1537                 for x in dir(cls)
1538                 if x.startswith('_' + prefix + '_')
1539             )
1540 
1541         super(InspectedValidator, cls).__init__(*args)
1542 
1543         cls._types_from_methods, cls.validation_rules = (), {}
1544         for attribute in attributes_with_prefix('validate'):
1545             # TODO remove inspection of type test methods in next major release
1546             if attribute.startswith('type_'):
1547                 cls._types_from_methods += (attribute[len('type_') :],)
1548             else:
1549                 cls.validation_rules[attribute] = cls.__get_rule_schema(
1550                     '_validate_' + attribute
1551                 )
1552 
1553         # TODO remove on next major release
1554         if cls._types_from_methods:
1555             warn(
1556                 "Methods for type testing are deprecated, use TypeDefinition "
1557                 "and the 'types_mapping'-property of a Validator-instance "
1558                 "instead.",
1559                 DeprecationWarning,
1560             )
1561 
1562         # TODO remove second summand on next major release
1563         cls.checkers = tuple(x for x in attributes_with_prefix('check_with')) + tuple(
1564             x for x in attributes_with_prefix('validator')
1565         )
1566         x = cls.validation_rules['check_with']['oneof']
1567         x[1]['schema']['oneof'][1]['allowed'] = x[2]['allowed'] = cls.checkers
1568 
1569         for rule in (x for x in cls.mandatory_validations if x != 'nullable'):
1570             cls.validation_rules[rule]['required'] = True
1571 
1572         cls.coercers, cls.default_setters, cls.normalization_rules = (), (), {}
1573         for attribute in attributes_with_prefix('normalize'):
1574             if attribute.startswith('coerce_'):
1575                 cls.coercers += (attribute[len('coerce_') :],)
1576             elif attribute.startswith('default_setter_'):
1577                 cls.default_setters += (attribute[len('default_setter_') :],)
1578             else:
1579                 cls.normalization_rules[attribute] = cls.__get_rule_schema(
1580                     '_normalize_' + attribute
1581                 )
1582 
1583         for rule in ('coerce', 'rename_handler'):
1584             x = cls.normalization_rules[rule]['oneof']
1585             x[1]['schema']['oneof'][1]['allowed'] = x[2]['allowed'] = cls.coercers
1586         cls.normalization_rules['default_setter']['oneof'][1][
1587             'allowed'
1588         ] = cls.default_setters
1589 
1590         cls.rules = {}
1591         cls.rules.update(cls.validation_rules)
1592         cls.rules.update(cls.normalization_rules)
1593 
1594     def __get_rule_schema(cls, method_name):
1595         docstring = getattr(cls, method_name).__doc__
1596         if docstring is None:
1597             result = {}
1598         else:
1599             if RULE_SCHEMA_SEPARATOR in docstring:
1600                 docstring = docstring.split(RULE_SCHEMA_SEPARATOR)[1]
1601             try:
1602                 result = literal_eval(docstring.strip())
1603             except Exception:
1604                 result = {}
1605 
1606         if not result and method_name != '_validate_meta':
1607             warn(
1608                 "No validation schema is defined for the arguments of rule "
1609                 "'%s'" % method_name.split('_', 2)[-1]
1610             )
1611 
1612         return result
